    {
      "Text": "Security update for Linux Kernel Live Patch 11 for SLE 12 SP1",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 3.12.67-60_64_24 fixes several issues.\n\nThe following security bugs were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2017-1000364: An issue was discovered in the size of the stack guard page on Linux, specifically a 4k stack guard page is not sufficiently large and can be 'jumped' over (the stack guard page is bypassed) (bsc#1039496).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
